job_description:
About Us Topsort is revolutionizing the e-commerce landscape as a leading provider of AI-driven, auction-based media monetization & advertising APIs. Exceptional technology is built by exceptional human beings.

We're an adtech company who advertising should be intuitive, intelligent, and honestly cool. We don't like creepy advertising, nor keyword bidding, nor are we cookie-obsessed (well only the chocolate ones).

The industry is changing. We think access to monetization should be democratized to all and advertising shouldn't make any brand or seller feel confused or overwhelmed.

We're looking for people who are willing to disrupt the normal (because we think it's boring, slow, and annoying), people who hate when a website has weird ads that pop up for holidays to Hawaii, and most importantly people who want to work in a team who make bold choices, have extra-ordinary opinions and can keep up our 100mph speed

We are seeking a motivated Senior Product Manager to join our Product team at Topsort. This role's primary goal will be leading product management and new requirements together with the product team and engineering team. You'll work closely on scaling the current product by incorporating user feedback, bringing ideas, and turning ideas into real product improvements

What this job will look like

Execute the product roadmap by overseeing the entire product lifecycle, including vision, planning, and execution;

Write product requirements that provide adequate technical details for developers and a clear overview for executives and non-technical team members;

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define technical and product requirements and create detailed specifications;

Participate in sprint planning and review meetings with development teams to ensure that technical and product requirements are met;

Collaborate with technical teams to identify and evaluate technical solutions, considering trade-offs and feasibility;

Continuously monitor and assess product performance to identify opportunities for improvements and drive innovation;

Maintain technical documentation, including architecture diagrams and specifications;

Support solutions and operations teams to ensure that products meet operational requirements;

Work in a fast-paced and innovative environment to drive product development and launch successful products.

What we are looking for

Minimum 5 years of experience in related roles in a B2B SaaS environment;

Proven track record of successfully launching and scaling products, especially complex SaaS and API products;

Strong organizational and communication skills with the ability to effectively communicate with executive-level stakeholders and manage Enterprise customers;

Data-driven decision-making abilities, familiarity with tools like Mixpanel, Looker, SQL and unafraid to learn and adapt to new tools;

Bachelor's degree highly desirable, preferably in Computer Science or a related field;

A team player mindset - Topsort's culture fosters a collaborative environment, where ownership and collaboration are valued.

Bonus Points

Previous experience in a fast-paced tech scale-up;

Knowledge of app development and API design;

Familiarity with Agile methodologies and tools (Scrum, Kanban, JIRA, etc.);

What's in it for you?

Medical, dental, and vision insurance (US employees);

Remote fist-company;

WeWork membership reimbursement & learning benefits;

Networking, conferences & industry-related events;

Mindfulness & Meditation Apps;

Anniversary & Birthday celebrations;

Stock Option plan;

Competitive USD salary;

Surrounded by awesome and intelligent peers - our team inspires each other

Are you ready to take your product design game to the next level at Topsort? Apply now and let's make waves together in the tech world

Topsort is an equal-opportunity employer. We celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees.

Do you want to change the world? At Cabify, that’s what we’re doing. We aim to make cities better places to live by improving mobility for the people living in them, connecting riders to drivers at the touch of a button. Maybe one day cities will be places where nobody needs a private car. But we’ve still got a long way to go...fancy joining us?

Founded in 2011, we have become the first Spanish tech ‘unicorn’. Our HQ is in Madrid but you can currently find us in 38 cities across Spain and Latin America. Every month, new members join our world-class team of passionate, smart and talented individuals with a hunger to challenge the status quo.

But no matter how quickly we grow or how big we become, we’re determined to keep our ‘start-up’ spirit. We are a confident, professional, charismatic and focused team, young at heart and proud to do things the right way. We like to think of ourselves as an ethical and innovative tech company that has created a business where everyone is treated fairly and respectfully, from our engineers to the drivers that use our platform. Moreover, we always comply fully with government regulations and respect local laws.

It’s been quite a ride so far, but in reality our journey has only just begun. If we’re going to turn our vision into a reality, we’re going to need plenty more bright, ambitious people to join us!

About the position:

The Head of Sales is responsible for leading the company’s B2B strategy and operations for Cabify Chile. In this position, the Head will define the Cabify's Chile vision and strategies for the B2B P&L, sales development and consolidation (in an efficient and effective way) according to our clients needs and market opportunities (corporate clients).

You will be responsible for developing and executing the planning since the clients needs definition, strategy validation, new services implementation, sales operations improvements, to the development of processes, teams, routines and projects to reach and consolidate an efficient and reliable growth in this cabify's B2B revenue stream across our different business units.

Your objective is to ensure our sustainable growth and to consolidate and maintain our leading position in the short and long term in this core audience in Cabify.

This is a critical role for Cabify’s business growth which reports directly to the General Manager for Chile.

How will you help us achieve our mission?
• Growing and optimizing the corporate revenue stream;
• Planning, structuring, managing and controlling our sales operations;
• Define forecast, strategy and its implementation (strategy to execution responsibility);
• Define and Implement efficient processes and standards;
• Define and implement the Commercial Strategy looking always for this business scale up focus;
• Integrate Cabify strategy according to Corporate Clients needs (customer centric working method);
• Implement and define new product/services according to the sales growth strategy;
• Ensure the best experience for our clients during, pre, sales and post sales;
• Develop analytical frameworks to support decision making in Sales Department;
• Evaluate risk and lead quality assurance efforts;
• Report an operational performance and implement improvements;
• Building, leading, and developing, a rockstar team;

How we would like you to be:
• Act as a co-owner: someone who works hard and is proud of what he/she does. Has initiative and acts by cooperating when something doesn't work. But most important of all, he has a vocation for service.
• Trust, communicate and develop: a person who listens and learns, is transparent and demands the same from others.
• Embrace and drive change: change creates new opportunities. Be the change we need to scale and improve even more.
• Analyze, innovate, and simplify: a person who solves the root of the problem and not their symptoms. Raise hypotheses and test them. Share data and not opinions. Innovate, creative, Make new mistakes and share them so we can learn from them. Throw out the obsolete, look for simplicity and scalable.
• Contribute and engage: someone who shares data to make the best decision. Make decisions and avoid overanalysis paralysis.
• Makes an impact: It seeks to produce added value for its actions. Think "done" is better than "perfect." Don’t reinvent the wheel. Delivery... and keeps getting better.
• Positive and humble attitude: Make sure that the people around you enjoy Mondays. Be constructive in the face of adversity and especially in the face of mistakes. Promote diversity and respect different opinions.

What we’re looking for:
• More than 5 years of experience in Sales or Business Development Departments;
• Previous experience in working in hyper-growth startups and/or fast-paced environments is a strong plus;
• Knowledge and expertise about Sales Development, Customer Success, Customer Development, Processes, Continuous Improvement Methods, New Services implementation, etc.
• At least 4 years of experience leading up-skilling teams,motivating the entire team while embodying Cabify’s values at all times;
• Hands-on experience in sales operations implementation and improvement;
• Hands-on experience in sales marketing/enablement implementation and improvement;
• Quantitative data analysis, deep actionable insights, modelling, and advanced test plan design and analysis experience;
• Critical thinking skills and business mindset;
• Experience working closely and communicating effectively with stakeholders in an ever-changing, rapid growth environment with tight deadlines;
• BSc/BA in Engineering, Management or relevant field. Postgraduate degree is a plus;
• Financial knowledge and different business models P&Ls expertise;
• Extensive knowledge in drive-Sheets

The good stuff:

We’re a company full of happy, motivated people and we never want that to change. Here are some more reasons why it rocks to be part of our family:
• Competitive salary based on experience
• Flexible work environment & hours
• Regular, fun team events
• Cabify staff discount
• Personal development programs
• Health insurance
• All the gear you need - just bring yourself
• And last but not least...free coffee & fruit!
